In a statement, President Obama congratulated Alassane Ouattara on his victory in the November 28 elections in Cote d'Ivoire. The Independent Electoral Commission, accredited observers, and the United Nations have all confirmed the result as credible. The President called on all parties, including incumbent President Laurent Gbagbo, to acknowledge and respect the result and allow the country to move towards a peaceful and democratic future. He also stated that the international community will hold accountable those who try to obstruct the democratic process.